<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1074">
There are $n$ sticks with some lengths. Your task is to modify the sticks so that each stick has the same length.<br />
<br />
You can either lengthen and shorten each stick. Both operations cost $x$ where $x$ is the difference between the new and original length.<br />
<br />
What is the minimum total cost?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The first input line contains an integer $n$: the number of sticks.<br />
<br />
Then there are $n$ integers: $p_1,p_2,\ldots,p_n$: the lengths of the sticks.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the minimum total cost.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
<li>$1 \le p_i \le 10^9$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5<br />
2 3 1 5 2</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>5</code>    </div>
